<Project>

  <!--
    NuGet audit suppression for CVE-2025-6965 / GHSA-2m69-gcr7-jv3q.

    The vulnerability is in the SQLite native library (< 3.50.2) bundled by
    SQLitePCLRaw.lib.e_sqlite3.* (pulled transitively via sqlite-net-pcl /
    SQLitePCLRaw.bundle_green). As of now there is NO patched SQLitePCLRaw
    release: the advisory flags all versions up to and including 2.1.11 (the
    latest), so a version bump cannot clear it.

    Risk assessment: ExamPlanner is a local, single-user app that only runs
    its own parameterized queries against its own database. The CVE requires
    attacker-controlled SQL where aggregate terms exceed available columns —
    a code path this app never exposes. Not reachable here.

    Action: revisit and remove this suppression once SQLitePCLRaw ships a
    build bundling SQLite >= 3.50.2, then upgrade.
  -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <NuGetAuditSuppress Include="https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-2m69-gcr7-jv3q" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
